# Reports Module Rules

## Report Entity

Report on content or users.

## Report Fields

- `id` - Unique identifier
- `reporterId` - ID of user who submitted report (foreign key to User)
- `targetType` - Target type (request, proposal, user, discussion)
- `targetId` - ID of target object
- `reason` - Reason (low-price, scam, inappropriate, spam, duplicate, other)
- `details` - Additional details
- `status` - Status (pending, reviewed, resolved, rejected)
- `createdAt` - Creation date
- `updatedAt` - Update date

## Report Reasons

- `low-price` - Suspiciously low price
- `scam` - Scam or fraud
- `inappropriate` - Inappropriate content
- `spam` - Spam
- `duplicate` - Duplicate content
- `other` - Other reason

## Report Statuses

- `pending` - Awaiting review
- `reviewed` - Under review
- `resolved` - Resolved
- `rejected` - Rejected (false report)

## Report Endpoints

- `POST /api/requests/:id/report` - Report request
- `POST /api/proposals/:id/report` - Report proposal
- `POST /api/users/:id/report` - Report user
- `POST /api/discussions/:id/report` - Report discussion
- `GET /api/admin/reports` - Get reports (admin only)
- `PATCH /api/admin/reports/:id` - Update report status (admin only)

## Report Service

- Create reports on various content types
- Track report status
- Link reports to target objects
- Admin can review and resolve reports

## Business Logic

- Users can report requests, proposals, users, or discussions
- Reports are stored with target type and ID
- Admin reviews reports and takes action
- Track report history and resolution
